  <bioghist id="a2" encodinganalog="545"> 
	 <head>Biographical Note</head> 
	 <p>Dr. Joseph Hoy Blazer was a New Mexican pioneer, dentist, merchant, and
		sawmill owner on the Tularosa River, within what became the Mescalero Apache
		Indian Reservation. Blazers's daughter Emma married Dr. John Howard Thompson, a
		physician on the Mescalero Reservation, then in El Paso, Texas. Blazer's son
		Armer carried on the mill business, while designing mechanical inventions and
		writing on local history. Armer's son, Paul, also researched local history and
		collected historic photographs.</p> 
  </bioghist> 
